3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFinland%20said%20a%20Russia-linked%20oil%20tanker%20was%20close%20to%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20its%20undersea%20cables.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIts%20president%20said%20that%20officials%20intervened%20about%2012%20minutes%20before%20the%20damage%20got%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20worse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20tanker%20is%20accused%20of%20being%20part%20of%20a%20Russian%20%26quot%3Bshadow%20fleet%26quot%3B%20sabotaging%20European%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFinnish%20President%20Alexander%20Stubb%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20his%20country%20had%20stopped%20the%20crew%20of%20a%20Russia-linked%20oil%20tanker%20just%20minutes%20before%20it%20caused%20catastrophic%20damage%20to%20undersea%20cables%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHad%20it%20continued%20for%20another%2012%20minutes%2C%20the%20carnage%20would%20have%20been%20much%20worse%20than%20the%20four%20basic%20cables%20that%20were%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Stubb%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DidrVFXUyICc%26ab_channel%3DAssociatedPress%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20reporters%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20this%20week's%20Baltic-focused%20NATO%20summit%20in%20Helsinki.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tanker%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinland-seized-oil-tanker-undersea-cable-cutting-russia-shadow-fleet-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEagle%20S%2C%20was%20seized%20in%20late%20December%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Finland%20probed%20recent%20damage%20to%20its%20Estlink-2%20power%20line%2C%20one%20of%20two%20vital%20cables%20carrying%20electricity%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20data%20cables%20were%20also%20severed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinnish%20investigators%20have%20accused%20the%20Eagle%20S%20crew%20of%20trying%20to%20sabotage%20the%20cables%20by%20dragging%20the%20ship's%20anchor%20for%20miles%20along%20the%20seabed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Finnish%20head%20of%20the%20investigation%2C%20Risto%20Lohi%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Foil-tanker-sabotage-crew-were-poised-cut-more-cables-when-caught-finland-says-2025-01-13%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20Eagle%20S%20would%20likely%20also%20have%20attempted%20sabotage%20on%20the%20other%20power%20cable%2C%20the%20Estlink-1%2C%20had%20police%20not%20boarded%20the%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20would%20have%20been%20an%20almost%20immediate%20danger%20that%20other%20cables%20or%20pipes%20related%20to%20our%20critical%20underwater%20infrastructure%20could%20have%20been%20damaged%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lohi%2C%20who%20is%20the%20chief%20of%20Finland's%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20Stubb%20said%20that%20Finland's%20security%20process%20for%20protecting%20the%20cables%20started%20with%20the%20private%20company%20overseeing%20them.%20If%20a%20cable%20is%20severed%2C%20the%20firm%20would%20alert%20the%20authorities%2C%20who%20then%20try%20to%20find%20possible%20ships%20around%20the%20location%20of%20the%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20that%20happens%2C%20you%20identify%20the%20ship%20and%20contact%20the%20ship.%20Number%20four%2C%20you%20stop%20the%20ship%2C%26quot%3B%20Stubb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStubb%20added%20that%20Finnish%20authorities%20would%20compel%20the%20ship%20to%20enter%20Finnish%20waters%2C%20where%20officers%20could%20then%20legally%20board%20the%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20process%20is%20set%20to%20change%20now.%20European%20members%20of%20NATO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nato.int%2Fcps%2Fen%2Fnatohq%2Fnews_232122.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20at%20the%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20would%20launch%20a%20new%20program%2C%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BBaltic%20Sentry%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20collectively%20patrol%20near%20Baltic%20Sea%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20surveillance%20program%20involves%20frigates%2C%20maritime%20aircraft%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20small%20fleet%20of%20naval%20drones%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20NATO's%20secretary-general%2C%20Mark%20Rutte%2C%20at%20the%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20into%20the%20Eagle%20S%20is%20of%20particular%20significance%20to%20the%20European%20Union%20because%20it's%20suspected%20for%20years%20that%20Russia%20has%20been%20intentionally%20trying%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-finds-giant-clue-backing-claim-russia-slicing-undersea-cables-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecovertly%20damage%20Western%20undersea%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Other%20cables%2C%20such%20as%20two%20fiber-optic%20data%20cables%20running%20between%20Finland%20and%20Germany%2C%20were%20cut%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Eagle%20S%20is%20registered%20in%20the%20Cook%20Islands%2C%20European%20officials%20say%20it's%20tied%20to%20Russia%20because%20it%20was%20carrying%2035%2C000%20tons%20of%20unleaded%20gasoline%20loaded%20in%20Russian%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20accused%20the%20ship%20of%20being%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-coalition-tracks-russia-shadow-fleet-with-ai-undersea-cables-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20%26quot%3Bshadow%20fleet%2C%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fa%3Eor%20a%20network%20of%20vessels%20with%20owners%20registered%20outside%20Russia%20that%20are%20actually%20carrying%20sanctioned%20Russian%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20denied%20being%20involved%20in%20any%20way%20with%20such%20sabotage.%20The%20Russian%20Foreign%20Ministry%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20comment%20request%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinland-12-minutes-undersea-cables-russia-linked-oil-tanker-damage-2025-1%5