58%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20is%20the%20company%20that%20launched%20the%20Windows%20operating%20system%20and%20ubiquitous%20office%20productivity%20programs%20like%20Word%2C%20Excel%2C%20and%20Powerpoint.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Ryder%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMicrosoft%20is%20a%20software%20company%20known%20for%20products%20like%20Windows%2C%20Microsoft%20365%2C%20and%20Xbox.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMicrosoft%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20software%20companies%20in%20the%20world%20by%20market%20cap.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMicrosoft%20was%20co-founded%20by%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20and%20the%20company%20is%20now%20led%20by%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20software%20companies%2C%20with%20annual%20revenues%20nearing%20%24250%20billion%20in%20recent%20years.%20Among%20its%20many%20products%20and%20platforms%20are%20the%20programs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-word%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20Word%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Microsoft%20Excel%2C%20used%20by%20private%20citizens%20and%20corporations%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20and%20the%20Windows%20operating%20system%2C%20the%20most%20widely-used%20computer%20OS%20by%20a%20vast%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20was%20founded%20in%20Albuquerque%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20in%201975%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Gates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Paul%20Allen%2C%20with%20the%20latter%20leaving%20Microsoft%20in%201983%20following%20a%20diagnosis%20of%20Hodgkin%20disease.%20Gates%20would%20stay%20on%20as%20CEO%20of%20the%20company%20until%202000%2C%20when%20he%20voluntarily%20stepped%20down%2C%20largely%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20charitable%20work%20with%20the%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGates%20was%20replaced%20by%20Steve%20Ballmer%20as%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20serving%20until%20he%20was%20in%20turn%20replaced%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-satya-nadella-career-rise%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESatya%20Nadella%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014.%20Under%20Nadella's%20guidance%2C%20the%20company%20has%20grown%20ever%20more%20profitable%2C%20though%20there%20have%20also%20been%20many%20massive%20layoffs%20across%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20in%20greater%20detail%20at%20Microsoft's%20history%2C%20its%20many%20products%20and%20services%2C%20its%20financial%20successes%20and%20stumbles%2C%20and%20the%20foundation%20its%20profits%20helped%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fdcd5f7d-2f3a-464c-83b4-6819f30c2607%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMicrosoft's%20history%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Henry%20Gates%20III%2C%20better%20known%20as%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20had%20a%20preternatural%20talent%20with%20software%2C%20writing%20his%20first%20programs%20while%20a%20young%20teenager%20growing%20up%20in%20Seattle%2C%20Washington.%20By%20the%20time%20he%20graduated%20high%20school%20and%20went%20off%20to%20Harvard%2C%20Gates%20had%20already%20formed%20a%20business%20partnership%20with%20his%20friend%20and%20Microsoft%20co-founder%20Paul%20Allen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20Bill%20Gates%20and%20Paul%20Allen%20lean%20against%20a%20desk%20in%20a%201970s%20office.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671ff1d001ea6d83dee4980a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Gates%20and%20Paul%20Allen%20were%20computer%20whizzes%20in%20high%20school%2C%20and%20eventually%20formed%20Microsoft%20together.%3Cp%3EDoug%20Wilson%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20data%20analysis%20venture%20called%20Traf-O-Data%20that%20employed%20computers%20in%20parsing%20through%20information%20collected%20by%20roadway%20traffic%20counters.%20Traf-O-Data%20was%20not%20a%20business%20success%2C%20but%20it%20was%20the%20precursor%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesfoundation.org%2Fabout%2Fleadership%2Fbill-gates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20Corporation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20Allen%20and%20Gates%20founded%20in%20the%20spring%20of%201975.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%20based%20in%20Albuquerque%2C%20as%20Gates%20and%20Allen%20had%20been%20working%20for%20the%20New%20Mexico-based%20company%20Micro%20Instrumentation%20and%20Telemetry%20Systems%2C%20the%20Microsoft%20headquarters%20moved%20to%20Bellevue%2C%20Washington%2C%20in%20early%201979%2C%20seeing%20its%20founders%20return%20to%20a%20location%20near%20their%20childhood%20turf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20year%2C%201980%2C%20was%20a%20pivotal%20one%20for%20Microsoft%20because%20the%20technology%20giant%20IBM%20awarded%20the%20company%20a%20contract%20that%20saw%20a%20Microsoft%20operating%20system%20used%20in%20the%20vaunted%20IBM%20Personal%20Computer%2C%20or%20PC.%20This%20was%20MS-DOS%2C%20the%20premier%20OS%20for%20several%20years%2C%20supplanted%20only%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-mark-zuckerberg-elon-musk-lesson-of-microsoft-windows-platforms-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWindows%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20in%201985%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20first%20graphic%20interface%20operating%20systems%20the%20world%20had%20ever%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWindows%20would%20become%20the%20dominant%20computer%20operating%20system%20over%20the%20next%20few%20decades%2C%20during%20which%20Microsoft%20also%20released%20software%20that%20would%20become%20wildly%20successful%2C%20such%20as%20the%20aforementioned%20Word%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%2