id%3D%5C%22b3d45888-6d16-4c12-9c52-2c82cbe8603f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMicrosoft%20in%20the%20gaming%20world%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20has%20been%20in%20the%20video%20game%20world%20since%201979%2C%20when%20%26quot%3BMicrosoft%20Adventure%26quot%3B%20was%20released.%20It%20was%20a%20text-based%20problem-solving%20game%20with%20a%20feel%20not%20unlike%20a%20%26quot%3BDungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Esession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%201980s%20and%20into%20the%201990s%2C%20the%20company%20would%20churn%20out%20many%20video%20games%2C%20but%20few%20were%20mainstream%20successes%20save%20for%20the%20many%20versions%20of%20%26quot%3BMicrosoft%20Flight%20Simulator%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20was%20first%20released%20in%201982.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20Microsoft%20got%20into%20the%20console%20gaming%20world%20that%20true%20gaming%20success%20arrived.%20Designed%20to%20compete%20with%20Sony's%20successful%20PlayStation%20video%20game%20console%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-xbox%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXbox%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20released%20in%202001%20and%20would%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20gaming%20platforms%20on%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Gates%20unveils%20the%20Xbox%20at%20a%20launch%20event%20in%202001.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671ff5c59b3250dbbcea9f4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221588%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20released%20the%20Xbox%20as%20a%20rival%20to%20Sony's%20Playstation%2C%20garnering%20immediate%20success.%3Cp%3EJeff%20Christensen%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20in%20its%20fourth%20generation%20of%20console%2C%20the%20Xbox's%20most%20popular%20games%20include%20the%20franchises%20%26quot%3BCall%20of%20Duty%2C%26quot%